‚úÖ Example E ‚Äî Distinct but with ORDER BY (Sorted Unique Results)
Get distinct cities sorted alphabetically:
SELECT DISTINCT city
FROM Customers
ORDER BY city ASC;

Result:
Delhi
Mumbai
Pune

‚úÖ KEY TAKEAWAYS (for You to Remember)
Use DISTINCT when you want unique values ‚Äî either single column or combination of columns.
SELECT DISTINCT cleans duplicates ‚Äî good for summary lists, dropdown data, unique counts.
For counting unique values, combine DISTINCT with aggregate functions (like COUNT(...)).
Be careful: duplicates are defined across all columns you list after DISTINCT.

Avoid unnecessary DISTINCT if you need full data or duplicates matter ‚Äî it can slow down queries.
